  "body": "Sometimes my node just stop sending transactions, I can use most of the commands, but sendTransaction just timeout.\r\n\r\neth.syncing return false\r\neth.blockNumber return the latest block\r\n\r\nhtop shows my server is not overloaded (8cores 20gb ram)\r\n\r\nIt works sometimes, but then it stops and keep bugged for some hours, it was working perfectly about a week ago, no modifications have been made on the server and no updates on the node.\r\n\r\nI'm trying to send the transaction from command line for test purposes, like:\r\n\r\neth.sendTransaction({from: \"0x46da24dbb9a19dafaf620a363396cecf20c95fed\",to: \"0x46da24dbb9a19dafaf620a363396cecf20c95fed\", value: \"0\"})\r\n\r\nbsc.log don't show anything anormal.\r\n\r\nAnyone experienced this issue?\r\n\r\nVersion: Version: Geth v1.0.7",
